{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853647983,"sessionID":"ses_286e015c3ffetU3z6nz1otpb4p","part":{"id":"prt_d79202c83001KGQ7hlvuTAZ0y3","messageID":"msg_d79200f6a001MATkfQXvqqa1x8","sessionID":"ses_286e015c3ffetU3z6nz1otpb4p","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-22ebef8e37a74b22b3a1e86a4e9fcbc5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: | Item | Value |\n5: |------|-------|\n6: | AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n7: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n8: | Language | Go |\n9: | Size | M |\n10: | Stage | ST-0 |\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: 实现 Router 模块的 JWT 认证与签发功能，包括：\n14: - JWT Token 生成与签发\n15: - JWT Token 验证中间件\n16: - Token 刷新机制\n17: \n18: ## Out of Scope\n19: - OAuth2 集成\n20: - 第三方身份提供商对接\n21: - 用户权限管理（RBAC）\n22: \n23: ## Dependencies\n24: - 待分析\n25: \n26: ## Deliverables\n27: | File | Description |\n28: |------|-------------|\n29: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWT 核心功能实现 |\n30: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT 单元测试 |\n31: | `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go` | 认证中间件 |\n32: \n33: ## Acceptance Criteria\n34: - [ ] JWT Token 签发功能正常\n35: - [ ] Token 验证中间件正确拦截无效请求\n36: - [ ] Token 刷新机制工作正常\n37: - [ ] 测试覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n38: \n39: ## References\n40: - 待补充\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Metadata\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n实现 Router 模块的 JWT 认证与签发功能，包括：\n- JWT Token 生成与签发\n- JWT Token 验证中间件\n- Token 刷新机制\n\n## Out of Scope\n- OAuth2 集成\n- 第三方身份提供商对接","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/spec.md","time":{"start":1775853647954,"end":1775853647981}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853647985,"sessionID":"ses_286e015c3ffetU3z6nz1otpb4p","part":{"id":"prt_d792030a10016KkOf46ViLsqG0","messageID":"msg_d79200f6a001MATkfQXvqqa1x8","sessionID":"ses_286e015c3ffetU3z6nz1otpb4p","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fc846fdb68e548b58fa8abac303837ff","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement JWT authentication and signing capabilities for the AgentCube Router module. This provides secure service-to-service communication and identity verification between Router and sandbox pods. The JWT component:\n6: \n7: 1. **Token Generation**: Creates signed JWT tokens with RS256 algorithm containing session/sandbox identity claims\n8: 2. **Key Management**: Generates RSA key pairs (2048-bit) for signing and verification\n9: 3. **Token Claims**: Embeds session_id, sandbox_id, namespace, name as standard claims with 5-minute expiration\n10: 4. **Issuer Identity**: Sets `agentcube-router` as standard issuer for service identification\n11: 5. **Key Persistence**: Supports PEM encoding/decoding for Kubernetes Secret storage\n12: 6. **Public Key Distribution**: Provides GetPublicKey for downstream verification\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In Scope\n17: \n18: | Deliverable | Description |\n19: |-------------|-------------|\n20: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager implementation with GenerateToken, key management, PEM encoding |\n21: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | Unit tests for token generation, parsing, expiration, key encoding |\n22: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | JWTSigningError type with APIStatus implementation |\n23: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | JWTManagerInterface definition |\n24: | RSA Key Generation | 2048-bit RSA keys for RS256 signing |\n25: | Token Expiration | 5-minute default expiration (jwtExpiration constant) |\n26: | PEM Encoding | encodePrivateKeyPEM, encodePublicKeyPEM, loadPrivateKeyPEM helpers |\n27: | Kubernetes Secret Support | IdentitySecretName, PrivateKeyDataKey, PublicKeyDataKey constants |\n28: \n29: ### Key Components\n30: \n31: ```\n32: pkg/router/\n33: ├── JWTManager (jwt.go)\n34: │   ├── privateKey: *rsa.PrivateKey (2048-bit)\n35: │   ├── publicKey: *rsa.PublicKey\n36: │   ├── GenerateToken(claims): RS256 signed JWT with exp, iat, iss + custom claims\n37: │   ├── GetPublicKey(): Returns public key for verification\n38: │   └── TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx): Placeholder for K8s Secret persistence\n39: │\n40: ├── Constants (jwt.go)\n41: │   ├── rsaKeySize = 2048\n42: │   ├── jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute\n43: │   ├── IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n44: │   ├── PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"\n45: │   ├── PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"\n46: │   └── IdentityNamespace = \"default\" (or AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env)\n47: │\n48: ├── PEM Helpers (jwt.go)\n49: │   ├── encodePrivateKeyPEM(key): PKCS1 PEM format\n50: │   ├── encodePublicKeyPEM(key): PKIX PEM format\n51: │   └── loadPrivateKeyPEM(data): Parse PKCS1 PEM to rsa.PrivateKey\n52: │\n53: └── JWTSigningError (errors.go)\n54: │   ├── Err: wrapped error\n55: │   ├── Status() = 500\n56: │   ├── Code() = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n57: │   └── Message() = \"jwt signing failed\"\n58: ```\n59: \n60: ### Out of Scope\n61: \n62: - Token validation middleware (not needed; Router only generates, sandboxes verify)\n63: - OAuth2/OIDC protocol implementation\n64: - Third-party identity provider integration\n65: - Refresh token mechanism\n66: - Token revocation/blacklist\n67: - Fine-grained RBAC permissions\n68: - HS256 symmetric signing (RS256 asymmetric is preferred for distributed verification)\n69: \n70: ## Impact Analysis\n71: \n72: ### Upstream Dependencies\n73: \n74: | Dependency | Impact |\n75: |------------|--------|\n76: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Core JWT library for token creation and parsing |\n77: | `crypto/rand` | Secure random number generation for RSA keys |\n78: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA key generation and signing |\n79: | `crypto/x509`, `encoding/pem` | PEM encoding for key storage |\n80: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Logging for TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret warning |\n81: | `os.Getenv` | AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE for IdentityNamespace |\n82: \n83: ### Downstream Consumers\n84: \n85: | Consumer | Usage |\n86: |----------|-------|\n87: | `Server.handleInvoke` | Calls jwtManager.GenerateToken with session/sandbox claims for sandbox/claim kinds |\n88: | `reverse_proxy.go` | JWT token added to Authorization header when proxying to sandbox |\n89: | Sandbox pods | Verify JWT using Router's public key (distributed via K8s Secret) |\n90: | `Server` struct | Stores *JWTManager for token generation |\n91: \n92: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n93: \n94: - **JWT Claims Schema**: session_id, sandbox_id, namespace, name claims are consumed by sandboxes; changing requires sandbox update\n95: - **Issuer Name**: `agentcube-router` is expected by verification logic; changing breaks trust\n96: - **Expiration Duration**: 5-minute jwtExpiration affects sandbox verification window\n97: - **Key Size**: 2048-bit RSA is expected; smaller keys may be rejected by validators\n98: - **Secret Name**: `picod-router-identity` Secret must exist for public key distribution\n99: \n100: ## Alternatives Considered\n101: \n102: ### Alternative 1: HS256 Symmetric Signing\n103: \n104: **Approach**: Use HMAC-SHA256 with shared secret key instead of RSA.\n105: \n106: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n107: |--------|------------|\n108: | Pros | Faster signing/verification; simpler key management (single secret) |\n109: | Cons | Secret must be shared with all verifiers; key rotation requires all services to update; less secure distribution |\n110: \n111: **Decision**: Rejected. RS256 asymmetric signing allows Router to keep private key secret while distributing public key to sandboxes. Key rotation only affects Router, not all verifiers.\n112: \n113: ### Alternative 2: Longer Token Expiration\n114: \n115: **Approach**: Use 24-hour or longer token expiration to reduce token generation overhead.\n116: \n117: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n118: |--------|------------|\n119: | Pros | Fewer token generations; simpler session handling |\n120: | Cons | Stale tokens persist longer; sandbox may accept requests after session ended; security risk |\n121: \n122: **Decision**: Rejected. 5-minute expiration aligns with short-lived sandbox sessions. Tokens naturally expire before or around session timeout (30 minutes default), reducing stale token acceptance.\n123: \n124: ### Alternative 3: JWT in Query Parameter\n125: \n126: **Approach**: Pass JWT token via URL query parameter instead of Authorization header.\n127: \n128: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n129: |--------|------------|\n130: | Pros | Simpler for HTTP clients without header support |\n131: | Cons | Token visible in URLs; logged in proxy/server logs; URL-encoded tokens break caching |\n132: \n133: **Decision**: Rejected. Authorization header (`Authorization: Bearer <token>`) is OAuth2/Bearer standard, keeps token out of URLs and logs.\n134: \n135: ### Alternative 4: External JWT Service\n136: \n137: **Approach**: Delegate JWT generation to external identity service (e.g., Auth0, Keycloak).\n138: \n139: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n140: |--------|------------|\n141: | Pros | Centralized identity management; standard OAuth2/OIDC support |\n142: | Cons | External dependency; network latency for each token; cost; overkill for service-to-service auth |\n143: \n144: **Decision**: Rejected. Router-to-sandbox auth is simple service identity, not user auth. Self-contained JWT generation keeps architecture simple and avoids external dependencies.\n145: \n146: ### Alternative 5: No JWT (Direct Service Account Auth)\n147: \n148: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes service account token for all authentication.\n149: \n150: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n151: |--------|------------|\n152: | Pros | K8s-native; no custom JWT code; automatic token rotation |\n153: | Cons | Service account tokens are long-lived (1 hour+); no sandbox-specific claims; shared across all pods with same SA |\n154: \n155: **Decision**: Rejected. Router JWT provides per-session claims (session_id, sandbox_id) for fine-grained sandbox identification. Service account tokens lack this granularity.\n156: \n157: ## Risks\n158: \n159: | Risk | Mitigation |\n160: |------|------------|\n161: | Private key leakage | Keep private key in Router memory; never log; use K8s Secret for persistence (read-only for sandboxes) |\n162: | Token replay attacks | Short 5-minute expiration; tokens tied to specific session/sandbox |\n163: | Clock drift causes validation failure | JWT library handles reasonable clock skew; sandboxes use jwt.WithLeeway() |\n164: | Key rotation disruption | TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret supports loading existing keys; generate new only on startup |\n165: | Public key unavailable to sandbox | Distribute via K8s Secret `picod-router-identity`; sandboxes mount as volume |\n166: | RSA key generation slow | Generate once at Router startup; reuse for all tokens |\n167: | Missing JWT claims | GenerateToken requires claims map; validation in sandbox verifies required fields |\n168: \n169: ## Implementation Notes\n170: \n171: 1. **Library**: `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` (latest stable)\n172: 2. **Algorithm**: RS256 (RSA Signature with SHA-256)\n173: 3. **Key Size**: 2048-bit RSA (balance of security and performance)\n174: 4. **Expiration**: 5 minutes (`jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`)\n175: 5. **Issuer**: `agentcube-router` (standard `iss` claim)\n176: 6. **Claims**: Standard (exp, iat, iss) + Custom (session_id, sandbox_id, namespace, name)\n177: 7. **Namespace**: `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` or from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env\n178: 8. **Secret Name**: `picod-router-identity` for K8s Secret containing PEM-encoded keys\n179: 9. **PEM Format**: Private key PKCS1, Public key PKIX (standard formats)\n180: 10. **Error Handling**: JWTSigningError wraps underlying error, returns 500 status\n181: \n182: ## References\n183: \n184: - [golang-jwt/jwt v5](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n185: - [RFC 7519 - JSON Web Token](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519)\n186: - [RFC 7518 - JSON Web Algorithms](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7518) (RS256)\n187: - `pkg/router/jwt.go` - Implementation\n188: - `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` - Test coverage\n189: - `pkg/router/doc.go` - JWTManagerInterface definition\n190: - `pkg/router/errors.go` - JWTSigningError type\n191: - `pkg/router/server.go:154-171` - JWT usage in handleInvoke\n192: - `deployment/client-go.md` - Kubernetes client reference (for Secret management)\n193: - `changes/AR-010/proposal.md` - Related Session Manager proposal\n\n(End of file - total 193 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement JWT authentication and signing capabilities for the AgentCube Router module. This provides secure service-to-service communication and identity verification between Router and sandbox pods. The JWT component:\n\n1. **Token Generation**: Creates signed JWT tokens with RS256 algorithm containing session/sandbox identity claims\n2. **Key Management**: Generates RSA key pairs (2048-bit) for signing and verification\n3. **Token Claims**: Embeds session_id, sandbox_id, namespace, name as standard claims with 5-minute expiration\n4. **Issuer Identity**: Sets `agentcube-router` as standard issuer for service identification\n5. **Key Persistence**: Supports PEM encoding/decoding for Kubernetes Secret storage\n6. **Public Key Distribution**: Provides GetPublicKey for downstream verification\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager implementation with GenerateToken, key management, PEM encoding |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775853647958,"end":1775853647983}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853647987,"sessionID":"ses_286e015c3ffetU3z6nz1otpb4p","part":{"id":"prt_d79203835001OKe8yCwksyL3e0","messageID":"msg_d79200f6a001MATkfQXvqqa1x8","sessionID":"ses_286e015c3ffetU3z6nz1otpb4p","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-61e0bfa7205342e4a38085bfdbcac86f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Data Structures (ST-1) ✓\n18: \n19: - [x] **T1.1**: Define JWT constants in `jwt.go`\n20:   - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n21:   - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n22:   - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n23:   - `PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"`\n24:   - `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n25:   - `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` (overridden by `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env)\n26:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n27:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration -v`\n28: \n29: - [x] **T1.2**: Define `JWTManager` struct in `jwt.go`\n30:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n31:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n32:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n33:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n34: \n35: - [x] **T1.3**: Define `JWTSigningError` in `errors.go`\n36:   - `Err error` field\n37:   - Implements `APIStatus` interface\n38:   - `Status() = 500`, `Code() = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"`\n39:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n40:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSigningError -v`\n41: \n42: ### Phase 2: JWT Generation (ST-2) ✓\n43: \n44: - [x] **T2.1**: Implement `NewJWTManager()` constructor\n45:   - Generate RSA 2048-bit key: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n46:   - Derive public key from private key\n47:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n48:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n49: \n50: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `GenerateToken(claims)` method\n51:   - Create JWT with standard claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n52:   - Merge custom claims into `jwt.MapClaims`\n53:   - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n54:   - Return signed token string or `JWTSigningError`\n55:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n56:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGenerateToken -v`\n57: \n58: - [x] **T2.3**: Implement PEM encoding helpers\n59:   - `encodePrivateKeyPEM(key)` - PKCS1 PEM encoding with \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\" block\n60:   - `encodePublicKeyPEM(key)` - PKIX PEM encoding with \"PUBLIC KEY\" block\n61:   - `loadPrivateKeyPEM(data)` - Parse PKCS1 PEM back to `*rsa.PrivateKey`\n62:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n63:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM -v`\n64: \n65: - [x] **T2.4**: Implement `GetPublicKey()` method\n66:   - Return `*rsa.PublicKey` for downstream verification\n67:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n68:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v`\n69: \n70: - [x] **T2.5**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` placeholder\n71:   - Log warning \"not in cluster, skipping secret persistence\"\n72:   - Return nil (placeholder for future K8s Secret persistence)\n73:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n74:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n75: \n76: ### Phase 3: JWT Verification (ST-3)\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.1**: Define `RouterClaims` struct\n79:   - Extend `jwt.RegisteredClaims`\n80:   - Custom fields: `SessionID string`, `SandboxID string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`\n81:   - JSON tags: `session_id`, `sandbox_id`, `namespace`, `name`\n82:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n83:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n84: \n85: - [ ] **T3.2**: Define additional JWT error types in `errors.go`\n86:   - `JWTValidationError` - code `JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED`, HTTP 401\n87:   - `JWTTokenExpiredError` - code `JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED`, HTTP 401, field `TokenID`\n88:   - `JWTTokenMissingError` - code `JWT_TOKEN_MISSING`, HTTP 401\n89:   - `JWTInvalidFormatError` - code `JWT_INVALID_FORMAT`, HTTP 401\n90:   - `JWTKeyLoadError` - code `JWT_KEY_LOAD_FAILED`, HTTP 500\n91:   - All implement `APIStatus` interface\n92:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n93:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v`\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `ValidateToken(tokenString)` method\n96:   - Parse token with public key verification\n97:   - Map jwt library errors to custom error types\n98:   - Return `*RouterClaims` on success\n99:   - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenExpired` → `JWTTokenExpiredError`\n100:   - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` → `JWTValidationError`\n101:   - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenMalformed` → `JWTValidationError`\n102:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n103:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement JWT error mapping helper\n106:   - `mapJWTParseError(err)` function\n107:   - Convert `jwt` library errors to router custom errors\n108:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n109:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMapJWTParseError -v`\n110: \n111: ### Phase 4: Authentication Middleware (ST-4)\n112: \n113: - [ ] **T4.1**: Define `JWTAuthMiddlewareConfig` struct\n114:   - `SkipPaths []string` - paths to bypass auth (e.g., `/health/*`)\n115:   - `TokenExtractor TokenExtractor` - custom token extraction function\n116:   - `KeyFunc jwt.Keyfunc` - key lookup function\n117:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n118:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.2**: Define `TokenExtractor` function type\n121:   - `type TokenExtractor func(r *http.Request) (string, error)`\n122:   - Extract token from Authorization header or other sources\n123:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n124:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n125: \n126: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `DefaultTokenExtractor(r)` function\n127:   - Get `Authorization` header from request\n128:   - Split by space, check format is \"Bearer <token>\"\n129:   - Return token string or `JWTTokenMissingError`/`JWTInvalidFormatError`\n130:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n131:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultTokenExtractor -v`\n132: \n133: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `JWTAuthMiddleware(jwtMgr, config)` function\n134:   - Create Gin middleware for JWT verification\n135:   - Skip paths matching `config.SkipPaths`\n136:   - Extract token via `config.TokenExtractor` or `DefaultTokenExtractor`\n137:   - Validate token via `jwtMgr.ValidateToken`\n138:   - Inject claims into `gin.Context` via `c.Set(\"jwt_claims\", claims)`\n139:   - Return appropriate error response on validation failure\n140:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n141:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddleware -v`\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement error response formatting in middleware\n144:   - Use `APIStatus` interface for error details\n145:   - Return JSON: `{\"error\": \"<message>\", \"code\": \"<code>\"}`\n146:   - Set HTTP status code from `Status()` method\n147:   - Call `c.Abort()` to stop request processing\n148:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n149:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddlewareErrors -v`\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement claims extraction helper `GetClaimsFromContext(c)`\n152:   - Retrieve claims from `gin.Context` via `c.Get(\"jwt_claims\")`\n153:   - Return `*RouterClaims` or nil if not present\n154:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n155:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestGetClaimsFromContext -v`\n156: \n157: ### Phase 5: Key Persistence (ST-5)\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T5.1**: Define `KeySecret` struct\n160:   - `Name string` - Secret name: `\"picod-router-identity\"`\n161:   - `Namespace string` - From `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`\n162:   - `Data map[string][]byte` - Keys: `\"private.pem\"` and `\"public.pem\"`\n163:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n164:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n165: \n166: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `KeyManager` struct\n167:   - `k8sClient kubernetes.Interface`\n168:   - `namespace string`\n169:   - `secretName string`\n170:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n171:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `NewKeyManager(k8sClient)` constructor\n174:   - Read namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env or default to `\"default\"`\n175:   - Set `secretName = IdentitySecretName`\n176:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n177:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewKeyManager -v`\n178: \n179: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `KeyManager.Exists(ctx)` method\n180:   - Check if Kubernetes Secret exists\n181:   - Call `k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Get(ctx, name, options)`\n182:   - Return `true` if exists, `false` if `IsNotFound` error\n183:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n184:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerExists -v`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `KeyManager.Load(ctx)` method\n187:   - Get Secret from Kubernetes\n188:   - Parse `secret.Data[\"private.pem\"]` via `loadPrivateKeyPEM`\n189:   - Return `*rsa.PrivateKey` or `JWTKeyLoadError`\n190:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n191:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerLoad -v`\n192: \n193: - [ ] **T5.6**: Implement `KeyManager.Store(ctx, privateKey)` method\n194:   - Encode private key via `encodePrivateKeyPEM`\n195:   - Encode public key via `encodePublicKeyPEM`\n196:   - Create Kubernetes Secret with `Data` map\n197:   - Call `k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Create(ctx, secret, options)`\n198:   - Return error on failure\n199:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n200:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerStore -v`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T5.7**: Update `JWTManager.TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` implementation\n203:   - Check if `k8sClient` is nil → skip (not in cluster)\n204:   - Call `KeyManager.Exists(ctx)`\n205:   - If exists: `KeyManager.Load(ctx)` → set private/public key\n206:   - If not exists: `KeyManager.Store(ctx, privateKey)` → persist new keys\n207:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n208:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerKeyPersistence -v`\n209: \n210: ### Phase 6: JWT Config (Optional) (ST-6)\n211: \n212: - [ ] **T6.1**: Define `JWTConfig` struct\n213:   - `Algorithm string` - default `\"RS256\"`, optional `\"HS256\"`\n214:   - `TokenExpiry time.Duration` - default `5 * time.Minute`\n215:   - `RefreshExpiry time.Duration` - default `30 * time.Minute`\n216:   - `Issuer string` - default `\"agentcube-router\"`\n217:   - `Audience []string` - optional\n218:   - `ClockSkew time.Duration` - default `30s`\n219:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n220:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n221: \n222: - [ ] **T6.2**: Implement `DefaultJWTConfig()` function\n223:   - Return config with default values\n224:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n225:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultJWTConfig -v`\n226: \n227: - [ ] **T6.3**: Update `NewJWTManager()` to accept optional `JWTConfig`\n228:   - `NewJWTManager(config *JWTConfig)` - nil config uses defaults\n229:   - Use config values for token expiration and issuer\n230:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n231:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerWithConfig -v`\n232: \n233: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n234: \n235: - [ ] **T7.1**: Add `ValidateToken` tests in `jwt_test.go`\n236:   - Test valid token verification\n237:   - Test expired token → `JWTTokenExpiredError`\n238:   - Test invalid signature → `JWTValidationError`\n239:   - Test malformed token → `JWTValidationError`\n240:   - Test token with custom claims extraction\n241:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n242:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v`\n243: \n244: - [ ] **T7.2**: Add JWT error type tests in `errors_test.go`\n245:   - Test `JWTValidationError` implements `APIStatus`\n246:   - Test `JWTTokenExpiredError` implements `APIStatus`\n247:   - Test `JWTTokenMissingError` implements `APIStatus`\n248:   - Test `JWTInvalidFormatError` implements `APIStatus`\n249:   - Test `JWTKeyLoadError` implements `APIStatus`\n250:   - File: `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n251:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v`\n252: \n253: - [ ] **T7.3**: Add middleware tests in `middleware_test.go`\n254:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with valid token\n255:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with invalid token\n256:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with missing token\n257:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with expired token\n258:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` skip paths\n259:   - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` Bearer format\n260:   - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` missing header\n261:   - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` invalid format\n262:   - Test `GetClaimsFromContext` extraction\n263:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n264:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuth -v`\n265: \n266: - [ ] **T7.4**: Add KeyManager tests in `jwt_test.go`\n267:   - Test `NewKeyManager` constructor\n268:   - Test `KeyManager.Exists` with mock client\n269:   - Test `KeyManager.Load` with mock secret\n270:   - Test `KeyManager.Store` with mock client\n271:   - Test `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` integration\n272:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n273:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManager -v`\n274: \n275: ### Phase 8: Integration & Coverage (ST-8)\n276: \n277: - [ ] **T8.1**: Integration test for full JWT flow\n278:   - Generate token → Validate token → Extract claims\n279:   - Verify claims match original input\n280:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n281:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTIntegration -v`\n282: \n283: - [ ] **T8.2**: Integration test for middleware chain\n284:   - Request → JWTAuthMiddleware → Handler with claims access\n285:   - Verify 401 on invalid token\n286:   - Verify 200 with claims injection on valid token\n287:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n288:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddlewareIntegration -v`\n289: \n290: - [ ] **T8.3**: Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n291:   - Run `go test ./pkg/router -cover`\n292:   - Identify uncovered code paths\n293:   - Add missing test cases\n294:   - File: `pkg/router/*_test.go`\n295:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -cover`\n296: \n297: - [ ] **T8.4**: All router tests pass\n298:   - `go test ./pkg/router -v`\n299:   - Fix any failing tests\n300:   - File: `pkg/router/*_test.go`\n301:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -v`\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## Task Dependencies\n306: \n307: ```\n308: Phase 1 (Completed)\n309:   T1.1 ── T1.2 ── T1.3\n310:      │\n311:      ▼\n312: Phase 2 (Completed)\n313:   T2.1 ── T2.2 ── T2.3 ── T2.4 ── T2.5\n314:      │\n315:      ▼\n316: Phase 3 (JWT Verification)\n317:   T3.1 ── T3.2 ──┬── T3.3 ── T3.4\n318:                 │\n319: Phase 4 (Middleware) ────────────────────────────┘\n320:   T4.1 ── T4.2 ── T4.3 ── T4.4 ── T4.5 ── T4.6\n321:      │\n322:      ▼\n323: Phase 5 (Key Persistence)\n324:   T5.1 ── T5.2 ── T5.3 ── T5.4 ── T5.5 ── T5.6 ── T5.7\n325:      │\n326:      ▼\n327: Phase 6 (JWT Config - Optional)\n328:   T6.1 ── T6.2 ── T6.3\n329:      │\n330:      ▼\n331: Phase 7 (Unit Tests)\n332:   T7.1 ── T7.2 ── T7.3 ── T7.4\n333:      │\n334:      ▼\n335: Phase 8 (Integration & Coverage)\n336:   T8.1 ── T8.2 ── T8.3 ── T8.4\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ---\n340: \n341: ## Verification Commands\n342: \n343: | Task | Verification Command |\n344: |------|----------------------|\n345: | T1.1, T1.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v` |\n346: | T1.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSigningError -v` |\n347: | T2.1, T2.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGenerateToken -v` |\n348: | T2.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM -v` |\n349: | T2.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v` |\n350: | T3.1 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n351: | T3.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v` |\n352: | T3.3, T3.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v` |\n353: | T4.1, T4.2 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n354: | T4.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultTokenExtractor -v` |\n355: | T4.4, T4.5, T4.6 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddleware -v` |\n356: | T5.1, T5.2, T5.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewKeyManager -v` |\n357: | T5.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerExists -v` |\n358: | T5.5 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerLoad -v` |\n359: | T5.6 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerStore -v` |\n360: | T5.7 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerKeyPersistence -v` |\n361: | T6.1 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n362: | T6.2, T6.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTConfig -v` |\n363: | T7.1 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v` |\n364: | T7.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v` |\n365: | T7.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuth -v` |\n366: | T7.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManager -v` |\n367: | T8.1 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTIntegration -v` |\n368: | T8.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddlewareIntegration -v` |\n369: | T8.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -cover` |\n370: | T8.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -v` |\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ## Acceptance Criteria\n375: \n376: - [ ] JWT Token 签发功能正常 (T2.1-T2.4 completed)\n377: - [ ] `ValidateToken` 方法正确验证 Token (T3.3)\n378: - [ ] JWT 错误类型完整定义 (T3.2)\n379: - [ ] Token 验证中间件正确拦截无效请求 (T4.4)\n380: - [ ] 跳过路径配置正常工作 (T4.1, T4.4)\n381: - [ ] Claims 正确注入到 Context (T4.6)\n382: - [ ] Kubernetes Secret 密钥持久化正常 (T5.3-T5.7)\n383: - [ ] 密钥加载与存储正常 (T5.4-T5.6)\n384: - [ ] 支持 RS256 算法 (已有)\n385: - [ ] 测试覆盖率 ≥ 80% (T8.3)\n386: - [ ] 所有验证命令通过 (T8.4)\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ## Files Modified/Created\n391: \n392: | File | Status | Description |\n393: |------|--------|-------------|\n394: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | Modified | Add ValidateToken, RouterClaims, KeyManager, JWTConfig |\n395: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | Modified | Add validation, KeyManager, integration tests |\n396: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Modified | Add JWT error types (ValidationError, ExpiredError, etc.) |\n397: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Modified | Add JWT error type tests |\n398: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Modified | Add JWTAuthMiddleware, TokenExtractor |\n399: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Modified | Add JWT middleware tests |\n400: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Modified | Add JWTManagerInterface updates if needed |\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ## Notes\n405: \n406: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n407: - **Phase 1-2 (ST-1, ST-2) already implemented**\n408: - **Dependencies**:\n409:   - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT signing and parsing (already used)\n410:   - `crypto/rsa` - RSA key operations (already used)\n411:   - `crypto/x509` - Key serialization (already used)\n412:   - `encoding/pem` - PEM encoding (already used)\n413:   - `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` - Kubernetes Secret persistence (optional)\n414:   - `k8s.io/klog/v2` - Logging (already used)\n415: - **Environment Variables**:\n416:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (optional, default \"default\") - Router identity namespace\n417: - **Security Notes**:\n418:   - RS256 preferred for asymmetric verification\n419:   - Private key stored in Kubernetes Secret (base64 encoded)\n420:   - Token expiration: 5 minutes (short-lived)\n421:   - Key rotation: future enhancement\n422: \n423: ---\n424: \n425: ## Implementation Timeline\n426: \n427: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n428: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n429: | Phase 1: Core Data Structures | T1.1-T1.3 | Completed | 100% |\n430: | Phase 2: JWT Generation | T2.1-T2.5 | Completed | 100% |\n431: | Phase 3: JWT Verification | T3.1-T3.4 | Not Started | 0% |\n432: | Phase 4: Authentication Middleware | T4.1-T4.6 | Not Started | 0% |\n433: | Phase 5: Key Persistence | T5.1-T5.7 | Not Started | 0% |\n434: | Phase 6: JWT Config (Optional) | T6.1-T6.3 | Not Started | 0% |\n435: | Phase 7: Unit Tests | T7.1-T7.4 | Not Started | 0% |\n436: | Phase 8: Integration & Coverage | T8.1-T8.4 | Not Started | 0% |\n437: \n438: **Total Progress: 25% Complete (8/32 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 438 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures (ST-1) ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Define JWT constants in `jwt.go`\n  - `rsaKeySize = 2048`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775853647962,"end":1775853647986}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853647993,"sessionID":"ses_286e015c3ffetU3z6nz1otpb4p","part":{"id":"prt_d79203491001VLo1kifk5joqPT","messageID":"msg_d79200f6a001MATkfQXvqqa1x8","sessionID":"ses_286e015c3ffetU3z6nz1otpb4p","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f63530c624da4e328269bf8c89e444f6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The Router JWT module provides token-based authentication for secure communication between Router and sandbox pods. It handles JWT token generation (signing), verification (validation), key management, and integration with the reverse proxy for Authorization header injection.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n23: │   Client SDK    │────▶│     Router      │────▶│   Sandbox Pod   │\n24: │ (Python/CLI)    │     │  (pkg/router)   │     │ (with picod)    │\n25: └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n26:                                │                         │\n27:                                │                         │\n28:                                ▼                         ▼\n29:                          ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n30:                          │   JWT Manager   │     │   Kubernetes    │\n31:                          │ (RS256 keys)    │     │   Secret Store  │\n32:                          └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### JWT Token Flow\n36: \n37: ```\n38: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n39: │                    JWT Generation Flow                               │\n40: │                                                                      │\n41: │  1. Request arrives at handleInvoke (server.go)                     │\n42: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐       │\n43: │                                                               │       │\n44: │  2. SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession → SandboxInfo         │       │\n45: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n46: │                                                               │       │\n47: │  3. Check kind == SandboxKind or SandboxClaimKind            │       │\n48: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n49: │                                                               │       │\n50: │  4. JWTManager.GenerateToken(claims)                         │       │\n51: │     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n52: │     │  Claims:                                         │     │       │\n53: │     │  - session_id: sandbox.SessionID                 │     │       │\n54: │     │  - sandbox_id: sandbox.SandboxID                 │     │       │\n55: │     │  - namespace: sandbox.SandboxNamespace           │     │       │\n56: │     │  - name: sandbox.SandboxName                     │     │       │\n57: │     │  - exp: now + 5min                               │     │       │\n58: │     │  - iat: now                                      │     │       │\n59: │     │  - iss: \"agentcube-router\"                       │     │       │\n60: │     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n61: │                                                               │       │\n62: │  5. RS256 Signing (rsa.PrivateKey)                           │       │\n63: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n64: │                                                               │       │\n65: │  6. ReverseProxyWrapper.Director                             │       │\n66: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n67: │     │  req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+jwt)        │       │\n68: │                                                               │       │\n69: │  7. Request forwarded to sandbox pod                         │       │\n70: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n71: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### JWT Verification Flow (Future Enhancement)\n75: \n76: ```\n77: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n78: │                    JWT Verification Middleware                       │\n79: │                                                                      │\n80: │  HTTP Request with Authorization header                              │\n81: │        │                                                             │\n82: │        ▼                                                             │\n83: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n84: │  │ JWTAuthMiddleware                                             │   │\n85: │  │  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  │   │\n86: │  │  │   Extract      │──│   Parse        │──│   Validate     │  │   │\n87: │  │  │   Token        │  │   Claims       │  │   Signature    │  │   │\n88: │  │  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘  │   │\n89: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n90: │        │                                                             │\n91: │        ▼                                                             │\n92: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n93: │  │ Claim Extraction → context.Set(\"session_id\", ...)             │   │\n94: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n95: │        │                                                             │\n96: │        ▼                                                             │\n97: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n98: │  │ Handler proceeds with authenticated context                    │   │\n99: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n100: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## Design\n106: \n107: ### Component Relationships\n108: \n109: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n110: |-----------|------|--------------|\n111: | `JWTManager` | RS256 key generation, token signing, key persistence | `rsa.PrivateKey`, Kubernetes client (optional) |\n112: | `JWTConfig` | JWT configuration (expiration, issuer, algorithm) | None |\n113: | `JWTAuthMiddleware` | Token verification middleware (future) | `JWTManager` |\n114: | `TokenRefresher` | Token refresh handler (future) | `JWTManager` |\n115: | `KeyManager` | Key persistence to Kubernetes Secret | `JWTManager`, Kubernetes client |\n116: \n117: ### Dependencies\n118: \n119: | Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n120: |---------|---------|-------------|\n121: | golang-jwt | JWT token generation and parsing | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` |\n122: | crypto/rsa | RSA key generation and signing | Go standard library |\n123: | crypto/x509 | Key serialization (PKCS1, PKIX) | Go standard library |\n124: | encoding/pem | PEM encoding for key storage | Go standard library |\n125: | crypto/rand | Secure random key generation | Go standard library |\n126: | Kubernetes client | Secret persistence (optional) | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` |\n127: | Klog | Logging | `k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## Data Structures\n132: \n133: ### JWTManager (`jwt.go`)\n134: \n135: ```go\n136: type JWTManager struct {\n137:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey  // 2048-bit RSA private key for signing\n138:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey   // Derived public key for verification\n139:     k8sClient  kubernetes.Interface  // Optional: for secret persistence\n140: }\n141: \n142: const (\n143:     rsaKeySize         = 2048                 // RSA key size in bits\n144:     jwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute      // Default token expiration\n145:     IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"  // Kubernetes Secret name\n146:     PrivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"        // Secret data key for private key\n147:     PublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"         // Secret data key for public key\n148: )\n149: \n150: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\"  // Overridden by AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### JWTConfig (Future Enhancement)\n154: \n155: ```go\n156: type JWTConfig struct {\n157:     Algorithm      string        // \"RS256\" (default) or \"HS256\"\n158:     TokenExpiry    time.Duration // Default: 5 minutes\n159:     RefreshExpiry  time.Duration // Default: 30 minutes (for refresh tokens)\n160:     Issuer         string        // Default: \"agentcube-router\"\n161:     Audience       []string      // Optional audience claim\n162:     ClockSkew      time.Duration // Allowed clock skew for validation\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ### JWT Claims Structure\n167: \n168: ```go\n169: type RouterClaims struct {\n170:     SessionID  string `json:\"session_id\"`  // Unique session identifier\n171:     SandboxID  string `json:\"sandbox_id\"`  // Sandbox pod identifier\n172:     Namespace  string `json:\"namespace\"`   // Kubernetes namespace\n173:     Name       string `json:\"name\"`        // Sandbox name\n174:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n175: }\n176: \n177: type RegisteredClaims struct {\n178:     ExpiresAt *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"exp,omitempty\"`  // Expiration timestamp\n179:     IssuedAt  *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"iat,omitempty\"`  // Issued at timestamp\n180:     NotBefore *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"nbf,omitempty\"`  // Not valid before\n181:     Issuer    string           `json:\"iss,omitempty\"`  // \"agentcube-router\"\n182:     Subject   string           `json:\"sub,omitempty\"`  // Optional subject\n183:     Audience  ClaimStrings     `json:\"aud,omitempty\"`  // Optional audience\n184:     ID        string           `json:\"jti,omitempty\"`  // JWT ID (unique)\n185: }\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ### TokenPair (Future Enhancement)\n189: \n190: ```go\n191: type TokenPair struct {\n192:     AccessToken  string `json:\"access_token\"`   // Short-lived token (5 min)\n193:     RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // Long-lived token (30 min)\n194:     ExpiresIn    int64  `json:\"expires_in\"`     // Seconds until expiration\n195:     TokenType    string `json:\"token_type\"`     // Always \"Bearer\"\n196: }\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ### Key Persistence Types\n200: \n201: ```go\n202: type KeySecret struct {\n203:     Name      string            // Secret name: \"picod-router-identity\"\n204:     Namespace string            // Namespace from AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n205:     Data      map[string][]byte // \"private.pem\" and \"public.pem\" keys\n206: }\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## API Contracts\n212: \n213: ### Existing: Token Generation (Internal)\n214: \n215: Token generation is performed internally during reverse proxy routing:\n216: \n217: ```go\n218: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n219: ```\n220: \n221: **Generated Claims:**\n222: ```json\n223: {\n224:   \"exp\": 1703001234,\n225:   \"iat\": 1703000934,\n226:   \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n227:   \"session_id\": \"sess-abc123\",\n228:   \"sandbox_id\": \"sbx-xyz789\",\n229:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n230:   \"name\": \"my-agent-runtime\"\n231: }\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ### Future: Token Issuance Endpoint\n235: \n236: | Method | Path | Description |\n237: |--------|------|-------------|\n238: | POST | `/auth/token` | Issue new access/refresh token pair |\n239: | POST | `/auth/refresh` | Refresh access token using refresh token |\n240: | GET | `/auth/public-key` | Retrieve public key for verification |\n241: \n242: ### Token Issuance Request/Response\n243: \n244: ```go\n245: type TokenRequest struct {\n246:     UserID   string                 `json:\"user_id\"`    // User identifier\n247:     Roles    []string               `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`  // Role claims\n248:     Metadata map[string]interface{} `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`  // Custom claims\n249: }\n250: \n251: type TokenResponse struct {\n252:     AccessToken  string `json:\"access_token\"`   // JWT access token\n253:     RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // JWT refresh token\n254:     ExpiresIn    int64  `json:\"expires_in\"`     // Expiration in seconds\n255:     TokenType    string `json:\"token_type\"`     // \"Bearer\"\n256: }\n257: \n258: type RefreshRequest struct {\n259:     RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // Valid refresh token\n260: }\n261: \n262: type PublicKeyResponse struct {\n263:     PublicKey string `json:\"public_key\"`  // PEM-encoded public key\n264:     Algorithm string `json:\"algorithm\"`   // \"RS256\"\n265:     Issuer    string `json:\"issuer\"`      // \"agentcube-router\"\n266: }\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ### Middleware Integration\n270: \n271: ```go\n272: type JWTAuthMiddlewareConfig struct {\n273:     SkipPaths      []string      // Paths to skip auth (e.g., \"/health/*\")\n274:     TokenExtractor TokenExtractor // Custom token extraction function\n275:     KeyFunc        jwt.Keyfunc   // Key lookup function\n276: }\n277: \n278: type TokenExtractor func(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n279: \n280: func DefaultTokenExtractor(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n281:     authHeader := r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\")\n282:     if authHeader == \"\" {\n283:         return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n284:     }\n285:     parts := strings.Split(authHeader, \" \")\n286:     if len(parts) != 2 || parts[0] != \"Bearer\" {\n287:         return \"\", ErrTokenInvalidFormat\n288:     }\n289:     return parts[1], nil\n290: }\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Key Management\n296: \n297: ### Key Generation Strategy\n298: \n299: ```\n300: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n301: │                    Key Lifecycle                                     │\n302: │                                                                      │\n303: │  1. Router Startup                                                   │\n304: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐       │\n305: │                                                               │       │\n306: │  2. Check Kubernetes Secret existence                        │       │\n307: │     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n308: │     │  k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets().Get(ctx, name)     │     │       │\n309: │     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n310: │                                                               │       │\n311: │  3a. Secret exists → Load existing keys                      │       │\n312: │      ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │       │\n313: │      │  loadPrivateKeyPEM(secret.Data[\"private.pem\"])   │    │       │\n314: │      │  publicKey = &privateKey.PublicKey               │    │       │\n315: │      └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │       │\n316: │                                                               │       │\n317: │  3b. Secret not exists → Generate new keys                   │       │\n318: │      ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │       │\n319: │      │  rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)              │    │       │\n320: │      │  encodePrivateKeyPEM, encodePublicKeyPEM         │    │       │\n321: │      └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │       │\n322: │                                                               │       │\n323: │  4. Store keys in Kubernetes Secret                          │       │\n324: │     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n325: │     │  k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets().Create(ctx, secret)│     │       │\n326: │     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n327: │                                                               │       │\n328: │  5. JWTManager ready for token operations                    │       │\n329: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n330: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### PEM Encoding Functions\n334: \n335: ```go\n336: func encodePrivateKeyPEM(key *rsa.PrivateKey) []byte {\n337:     return pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n338:         Type:  \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\",\n339:         Bytes: x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey(key),\n340:     })\n341: }\n342: \n343: func encodePublicKeyPEM(key *rsa.PublicKey) []byte {\n344:     bytes, err := x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey(key)\n345:     if err != nil {\n346:         return nil\n347:     }\n348:     return pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n349:         Type:  \"PUBLIC KEY\",\n350:         Bytes: bytes,\n351:     })\n352: }\n353: \n354: func loadPrivateKeyPEM(data []byte) (*rsa.PrivateKey, error) {\n355:     block, _ := pem.Decode(data)\n356:     if block == nil {\n357:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n358:     }\n359:     return x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey(block.Bytes)\n360: }\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ### Secret Structure\n364: \n365: ```yaml\n366: apiVersion: v1\n367: kind: Secret\n368: metadata:\n369:   name: picod-router-identity\n370:   namespace: ${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE:-default}\n371: type: Opaque\n372: data:\n373:   private.pem: <base64-encoded RSA private key>\n374:   public.pem: <base64-encoded RSA public key>\n375: ```\n376: \n377: ---\n378: \n379: ## Error Handling\n380: \n381: ### Custom Error Types (`errors.go`)\n382: \n383: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Code | Message | Condition |\n384: |------------|-------------|------|---------|-----------|\n385: | `JWTSigningError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | \"jwt signing failed\" | Token signing failure |\n386: | `JWTValidationError` | 401 | `JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED` | \"jwt validation failed\" | Token verification failure |\n387: | `JWTTokenExpiredError` | 401 | `JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED` | \"jwt token expired\" | Token past expiration |\n388: | `JWTTokenMissingError` | 401 | `JWT_TOKEN_MISSING` | \"jwt token missing\" | No Authorization header |\n389: | `JWTInvalidFormatError` | 401 | `JWT_INVALID_FORMAT` | \"invalid authorization header format\" | Malformed header |\n390: | `JWTKeyLoadError` | 500 | `JWT_KEY_LOAD_FAILED` | \"jwt key load failed\" | Key loading failure |\n391: \n392: ### Error Type Definitions\n393: \n394: ```go\n395: type JWTSigningError struct {\n396:     Err error\n397: }\n398: \n399: func (e *JWTSigningError) Error() string {\n400:     return \"jwt signing failed: \" + e.Err.Error()\n401: }\n402: \n403: func (e *JWTSigningError) Status() int { return 500 }\n404: func (e *JWTSigningError) Code() string { return \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\" }\n405: func (e *JWTSigningError) Message() string { return \"jwt signing failed\" }\n406: \n407: type JWTTokenExpiredError struct {\n408:     TokenID string\n409: }\n410: \n411: func (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Error() string {\n412:     return \"jwt token expired: \" + e.TokenID\n413: }\n414: \n415: func (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Status() int { return 401 }\n416: func (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Code() string { return \"JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED\" }\n417: func (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Message() string { return \"jwt token expired\" }\n418: ```\n419: \n420: ### Error Response Format\n421: \n422: ```json\n423: {\n424:   \"error\": \"<message>\",\n425:   \"code\": \"<error code>\"\n426: }\n427: ```\n428: \n429: ### JWT Parsing Errors Mapping\n430: \n431: | jwt.Parse Error | Router Error |\n432: |------------------|--------------|\n433: | `jwt.ErrTokenExpired` | `JWTTokenExpiredError` |\n434: | `jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` | `JWTValidationError` |\n435: | `jwt.ErrTokenMalformed` | `JWTValidationError` |\n436: | `jwt.ErrTokenNotValidYet` | `JWTValidationError` |\n437: \n438: ---\n439: \n440: ## Testing Strategy\n441: \n442: ### Test Coverage Goals\n443: \n444: | Component | Coverage Target | Key Test Cases |\n445: |-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n446: | `jwt.go` | 80%+ | Key generation, token signing, claim merging, expiration, PEM encoding/decoding |\n447: | `middleware.go` (auth) | 90%+ | Token extraction, validation flow, error responses, path skipping |\n448: | `KeyManager` | 85%+ | Secret creation, key loading, key rotation |\n449: \n450: ### Unit Tests (`jwt_test.go`)\n451: \n452: | Test | Description |\n453: |------|-------------|\n454: | `TestNewJWTManager` | Verify RSA key generation (2048-bit) |\n455: | `TestJWTManagerGenerateToken` | Token generation with custom claims, verify claims present |\n456: | `TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration` | Verify exp claim is approximately 5 minutes from now |\n457: | `TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey` | Verify public key retrieval for verification |\n458: | `TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM` | PEM encoding contains \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\" |\n459: | `TestEncodePublicKeyPEM` | PEM encoding contains \"PUBLIC KEY\" |\n460: | `TestLoadPrivateKeyPEM` | Load PEM data back to RSA key, verify key equality |\n461: | `TestLoadPrivateKeyPEMInvalid` | Invalid PEM data returns error |\n462: | `TestJWTSigningError` | Error type methods (Error, Status, Code, Message) |\n463: \n464: ### Integration Test Scenarios\n465: \n466: | Scenario | Description |\n467: |----------|-------------|\n468: | Key persistence | Generate → Store in K8s Secret → Restart → Load existing keys |\n469: | Token flow | Generate token → Verify with public key → Extract claims |\n470: | Proxy integration | Request → JWT generated → Authorization header set → Forwarded |\n471: | Secret namespace | AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env override for Secret location |\n472: \n473: ### Test Utilities\n474: \n475: ```go\n476: type MockJWTManager struct {\n477:     GenerateFunc func(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n478:     VerifyFunc   func(tokenString string) (*RouterClaims, error)\n479:     PublicKey    *rsa.PublicKey\n480: }\n481: \n482: type MockKeyManager struct {\n483:     StoreFunc  func(ctx context.Context, privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey) error\n484:     LoadFunc   func(ctx context.Context) (*rsa.PrivateKey, error)\n485:     ExistsFunc func(ctx context.Context) (bool, error)\n486: }\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ### Benchmarks\n490: \n491: ```go\n492: func BenchmarkJWTGenerateToken(b *testing.B) {\n493:     jwtMgr, _ := NewJWTManager()\n494:     claims := map[string]interface{}{\n495:         \"session_id\": \"test-session\",\n496:         \"sandbox_id\": \"test-sandbox\",\n497:     }\n498:     b.ResetTimer()\n499:     for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n500:         jwtMgr.GenerateToken(claims)\n501:     }\n502: }\n503: \n504: func BenchmarkJWTVerifyToken(b *testing.B) {\n505:     // Measure token verification performance\n506: }\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## Implementation Checklist\n512: \n513: - [x] `JWTManager` struct with RSA 2048-bit key pair\n514: - [x] `GenerateToken(claims)` method with RS256 signing\n515: - [x] Standard claims: exp (5min), iat, iss (\"agentcube-router\")\n516: - [x] PEM encoding functions for private/public keys\n517: - [x] `GetPublicKey()` method for verification\n518: - [x] `JWTSigningError` custom error type\n519: - [ ] `ValidateToken(tokenString)` method for verification\n520: - [ ] `JWTAuthMiddleware` for incoming request authentication\n521: - [ ] Key persistence to Kubernetes Secret\n522: - [ ] Key rotation support\n523: - [ ] Token refresh endpoint\n524: - [ ] Public key distribution endpoint\n525: - [ ] Clock skew tolerance configuration\n526: \n527: ---\n528: \n529: ## Validation Rules\n530: \n531: 1. RSA key size must be 2048 bits (minimum for RS256 security)\n532: 2. Token expiration defaults to 5 minutes (short-lived for sandbox communication)\n533: 3. Issuer claim must be \"agentcube-router\" (hardcoded)\n534: 4. Private key stored in PKCS1 PEM format\n535: 5. Public key stored in PKIX PEM format\n536: 6. Secret name: `picod-router-identity`\n537: 7. Namespace: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env or `default`\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Security Considerations\n542: \n543: ### Key Storage\n544: - Private key stored in Kubernetes Secret (base64 encoded)\n545: - Secret should be mounted only in Router pod\n546: - Consider using sealed secrets for GitOps deployments\n547: \n548: ### Token Lifetime\n549: - Access tokens expire in 5 minutes (short-lived)\n550: - Tokens are single-use per request (forwarded to sandbox)\n551: - No token caching in Router\n552: \n553: ### Algorithm Security\n554: - RS256 preferred over HS256 (asymmetric, verifiable without secret)\n555: - Private key never shared with sandbox pods\n556: - Public key can be distributed to verification endpoints\n557: \n558: ### Key Rotation\n559: - Generate new keys: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n560: - Store new keys in Secret with versioned name\n561: - Sandbox pods need updated public key for verification\n562: \n563: ---\n564: \n565: ## Open Questions\n566: \n567: 1. **Token Blacklist**: Should revoked sessions invalidate tokens immediately?\n568:    - Current: Tokens expire naturally after 5 minutes\n569:    - Alternative: Redis-backed blacklist for immediate revocation\n570: \n571: 2. **Multi-tenancy**: Should different namespaces use different keys?\n572:    - Current: Single key pair for all namespaces\n573:    - Alternative: Per-namespace key secrets\n574: \n575: 3. **Key Rotation Strategy**: When and how should keys rotate?\n576:    - Current: Keys generated once at startup\n577:    - Alternative: Scheduled rotation (weekly/monthly) with overlap period\n578: \n579: 4. **Token Audience**: Should tokens include audience claim?\n580:    - Current: No audience restriction\n581:    - Alternative: `aud: [\"sandbox-pod\"]` for target verification\n582: \n583: ---\n584: \n585: ## References\n586: \n587: - `jwt.go` — Current JWT implementation\n588: - `server.go:154-171` — Token generation in handleInvoke\n589: - `reverse_proxy.go:41-43` — Authorization header injection\n590: - `errors.go:63-81` — JWTSigningError definition\n591: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — AuthModeType constants\n592: - [RFC 7519 — JSON Web Token (JWT)](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519)\n593: - [RFC 7518 — JSON Web Algorithms (JWA)](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7518)\n594: - [golang-jwt/jwt v5](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n\n(End of file - total 594 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe Router JWT module provides token-based authentication for secure communication between Router and sandbox pods. It handles JWT token generation (signing), verification (validation), key management, and integration with the reverse proxy for Authorization header injection.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","time":{"start":1775853647960,"end":1775853647990}}}}
